spans.text: Disturbs the stillness of the grove
To the wild beach distracted flies , Or cheerless through the desert strays
While fearful echoes burst around , On some cold stone he leans his head
pale Misfortune's haggard train , Sad luxury ! delight to stray
all art My passion's force would meanly prove
My passion's force would meanly prove
the joys that once were mine
all my hopes of future bliss
each woman faithless prove , And each fond lover
